<hr /><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="lai-one"><h2></h2></header><div class="lai-no"><div class="lai-img-c lai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="student holding colonials sign" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/ColonialSign_AdmissionsandAidmainimage_Move_IN_UP_WLA_2009-7850_CUTOUT.jpg" /></p><figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="lai-copy lai-three"><p>At the George Washington University (GW), #OnlyatGW is not just a hashtag&mdash;it is our way of life. Living and learning in the heart of D.C. provides our students opportunities and experiences unlike anywhere else. Inside the classroom, you&rsquo;ll sit next to peers from all over the world and learn from faculty who are not only experts in their fields, but who also might be world-famous artists, policy-makers or dignitaries.&nbsp;</p><p>At GW, learning doesn&rsquo;t stop when class is over. It&#39;s the reason you&rsquo;re here and will be a part of everything you&rsquo;ll do. You can use our resources to forge your own path forward. You might find a dream internship at a non-profit or the White House, volunteer to better our city, run into government leaders on campus, or even study on the steps of monuments that tourists flock to. You&rsquo;ll not only live and learn at the center of our nation&rsquo;s capital, but you&rsquo;ll be a central part of it no matter your path.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul class="justifyButtons"><li><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://undergraduate.admissions.gwu.edu/" target="_blank">Office of Undergraduate Admissions</a></span></li><li><span class="reg-button darkblue"><a href="https://graduate.admissions.gwu.edu/" target="_blank">Office of Graduate Admissions</a></span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div></article></div></div></div><div class="container"><div class="row test-l-f"><div class="col-md-12 doodad"><hr /></div></div><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><div class="test-r clearfix"><div class="test-img-right"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="Anthony Abron" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/AnthonyAbron_AdmissionsandAidtestimonial_Anthony_Abron_UP_2016_WLA_6110.jpg" style="height:340px; width:352px" /></p></figure><div class="name-block light"><p class="name">Anthony Abron</p><p class="affi">Class of 2018<br />
								Majors: Music &amp; Political Communication</p></div></div><div class="test-r-copy"><blockquote class="test-r-quote"><p class="quote"><span class="testimonial-light">&ldquo;GW is a great spot if you know what you want to do, but also if you don&#39;t. It&#39;s going to open your eyes to so many different avenues. I wanted a place where I could seamlessly fit into the city and the environment of the school. I think for me there&#39;s a whole bunch of passions out there and GW is the place where I can funnel them all.&rdquo;</span></p></blockquote></div></div></article></div></div><div><p>&nbsp;</p><ul class="justifyButtons"><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://undergraduate.admissions.gwu.edu/apply-gw" target="_blank">Apply as an Undergraduate</a></span></li><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="reg-button darkblue"><a href="https://undergraduate.admissions.gwu.edu/visit-gw" target="_blank">Undergraduate Visits</a></span></li><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="ghost-button reg-button darkblue"><a href="https://undergraduate.admissions.gwu.edu/financial-aid" target="_blank">Undergraduate Costs &amp; Aid</a></span></li></ul></div><div class="row test-l-u"><div class="col-md-12 doodad-not"><hr /></div></div></div><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="rai-one"><h2>Find Your Program</h2></header><div class="rai-no"><div class="rai-img-c rai-two"><figure aria-labelledby="enlv-caption" style="position:relative;width: 375px; padding: 0;"><img alt="GW has more than 70 undergraduate majors and more than 200 graduate programs at the certificate, master's and doctoral levels" class="enlivenem" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/70majors.svg" /><figcaption id="enlv-caption" style="position:absolute;left:-9000px;">GW has more than 70 undergraduate majors and more than 200 graduate programs at the certificate, master&#39;s and doctoral levels</figcaption></figure></div><div class="rai-copy rai-three"><p>Whether you want to build robots, study sea lions at the National Zoo, work with world-renowned artists, develop a digital strategy for a political campaign or study Shakespeare, you&rsquo;ll be right at home in a GW classroom. Our programs of study are as diverse as our Colonial community&mdash;from biomedical engineering to dance, political science to archaeology, you can find the program you&rsquo;ve been searching for and use it to start doing what you always wanted to. &nbsp;</p><p>No matter your interest or situation in life, GW has a program for you. In our 10 schools and colleges you can find more than 100 undergraduate programs and more than 230 graduate programs at the certificate, master&rsquo;s and doctoral levels. You could study in the center of D.C., in Virginia at our <a href="/virginia-science-technology-campus">Virginia Science and Technology campus</a> or at one of our <a href="/online-virginia-academic-centers">graduate education centers</a> in Arlington or Alexandria. If these options don&rsquo;t work for you, you can study from home through one of our more than 100 <a href="/online-virginia-academic-centers">online programs</a>.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div></article></div></div></div><ul class="justifyButtons"><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="http://programs.gwu.edu/undergraduate" target="_blank">Undergraduate Programs</a></span></li><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="reg-button darkblue"><a href="http://programs.gwu.edu/graduate" target="_blank">Graduate Programs</a></span></li><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="ghost-button reg-button darkblue"><a href="/schools-colleges">Schools &amp; Colleges</a> </span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="container"><div class="row test-l-f"><div class="col-md-12 doodad"><hr /></div></div><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><div class="test-l clearfix"><div class="test-img-left"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="Brooke Pearson" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/BrookePearson_Admissionsaid_Testimonial.jpg" style="height:340px; width:352px" /></p></figure><div class="name-block light"><p class="name">Brooke Pearson</p><p class="affi">Master of International Policy and Practice, 2016</p></div></div><div class="test-copy"><blockquote class="test-l-quote"><p class="quote"><span class="testimonial-light">&ldquo;</span><span class="testimonial-light">Grad school at GW is ideal for someone who is balancing work and life. But it&rsquo;s also ideal for someone who is passionate about something and wants to dig deep and take specific classes to make them the leader that they want to become.&rdquo;</span></p></blockquote></div></div></article></div></div><div><p>&nbsp;</p><ul class="justifyButtons"><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://graduate.admissions.gwu.edu/step-step-application-process" target="_blank">Apply as a Graduate</a></span></li><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="reg-button darkblue"><a href="https://graduate.admissions.gwu.edu/visits-events" target="_blank">Graduate Visits</a></span></li><li style="max-width:300px;"><span class="ghost-button reg-button darkblue"><a href="https://studentaccounts.gwu.edu/graduate-tuition" target="_blank">Graduate Costs &amp; Aid</a></span></li></ul></div></div><hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="lai-one"><h2>Cross Time Zones to Become a Colonial</h2></header><div class="lai-no"><div class="lai-img-c lai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="more than 3,700 international students hailing from more than 130 countries" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/InternationalStudents_Academics_DSC_0216.jpg" /></p><figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="lai-copy lai-three"><p>With more than 3,700 international students hailing from more than 130 countries, GW&#39;s community thrives off of varied perspectives and experiences. In the classroom, students and faculty encourage each other to grow and expand their thinking beyond textbooks. Here you won&#39;t just read about current events and&nbsp;history&mdash;you&#39;ll enter discussions with classmates who have experienced them in their home country. We welcome you to share your culture and contribute new ideas about your passions, both the ones you know and those you can&#39;t wait to be exposed to at GW.</p><ul class="justifyButtons"><li><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://undergraduate.admissions.gwu.edu/international-application-process" target="_blank">Apply as an International Student</a></span></li><li><span class="ghost-button reg-button darkblue"><a href="https://internationalservices.gwu.edu/" target="_blank">International Services Office</a></span></li></ul></div></div></article></div></div></div><div class="row test-l-u"><div class="col-md-12 doodad-not">&nbsp;</div></div><hr /><h2>Expanded Learning Opportunities</h2><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-4 pos-one"><article><p class="col-img"><img alt="students standing writing at white board" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/Studentsatboard_AdmissionsandAid_gradenrollment_UP_206_LRW-3749-%281%291.jpg" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"><a href="/online-virginia-academic-centers"><b id="docs-internal-guid-8a806d8e-997a-a417-8fb0-5b259f53bc1f">Online &amp; Distance Learners</b></a></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>Our campus community expands beyond Washington, D.C. While you can find programs at one of our graduate education centers in Arlington or Alexandria, VA, you can also study from anywhere, at any time, by enrolling in one of our online programs. Regardless of where you study, you&#39;re a Colonial and an important member of our community. You&rsquo;ll benefit from access to our campus, the city and our vast alumni network.</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div><div class="col-md-4 pos-two"><article><p class="col-img"><img alt="GW pre-college students" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/Studentsincity_AdmissionsandAid_caminos_LRW-1099.jpg" /></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"><a href="https://summer.gwu.edu/precollege" target="_blank"><b id="docs-internal-guid-8a806d8e-997a-cfab-9f21-3e32c5bcbc1d">Pre-College Students</b></a></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>As a high school student, our pre-college programs allow you to experience academic life in college before you get here, learn more about your area of interest and meet other students from all over the world. If you&rsquo;re still deciding on college and interested in learning in Washington, D.C., we have programs for you from the arts and business to history, STEM and more. You&rsquo;ll have all the advantages that GW students do during the summer through our on-campus or online pre-college courses.&nbsp;</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div><div class="col-md-4 pos-three"><article><p class="col-img"><img alt="Group of students laughing" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/SummerStudents_AdmissionsandAid_126182_EG_00134_v2.jpg" /></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"><a href="https://summer.gwu.edu/" target="_blank"><b id="docs-internal-guid-8a806d8e-997a-e9d3-e117-e232900ff3ea">Summer Students</b></a></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>Spend your summer at GW to earn credit and take advantage of new cultures, either in D.C. or around the globe. You can find specific summer programs to enroll in or institutes to attend during the summer months on our campus. Our institutes, ranging from Health Promotion &amp; Disease Prevention in Minority Communities to Japanese Language &amp; Culture, are available to current GW and visiting students. We also offer short-term study abroad opportunities through our schools and colleges that will take you across the world to immerse yourself in academics and culture.</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div></div></div>    </div>
